This paper discusses a wireless network with distributed autonomous behavior, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also proposes an algorithm for self-tuning medium access probability, which involves control theory (cs.SY) and mathematical optimization (cs.MA). Finally, the paper discusses the scalability of the proposed algorithm, which relates to distributed computing (cs.DC).
